cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CL

This paper proposes a novel formulation for learning a hierarchical, disentangled object representation and a dynamics model from unlabeled videos. The focus is on computer vision tasks such as object part segmentation, hierarchical structure recognition, and motion prediction. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as unsupervised learning, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a structural descriptor that composes low-level concepts into a hierarchical structure, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves robotics applications such as modeling system dynamics, which suggests that it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques such as layered image representation, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
